docs.text: it is december 31 , 1981 and the big party is at monica's ( martha plimpton ) house .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but no one has arrived yet .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: her 8 invited guests and several people that they have picked throughout the evening are wandering the streets of new york city in various groups .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: some of them know each other through their common bond of having slept with monica , and some are total strangers .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but they all are to face their own personal neuroses before night's end .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: those who are invited are the ones that have the issues .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is up to those who aren't to help them come to terms .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: first there is eric ( brian mccardie ) who is a former boyfriend of monica's and is just getting over the heartbreak of their relationship terminating prematurely because of his sexual performance , or lack thereof .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he is one of the most bland characters , in a film full of dullness , because he is so utterly predictable and stereotypical , a common trait of this poor production .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: bridget ( nicole parker ) and caitlyn ( angela featherstone ) who are both extremely sensuous young women looking for someone to handle their desires on new year's eve and tag along to the party with them .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they stumble across a nameless bartender ( ben affleck ) who is the one truly perfect character in a film of imperfections .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he is nether sexually deprived , nor uncertain about his future , as he is in law school .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his lack of flaws is both boring , unrealistic and painful to watch .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as bridget and caitlyn make passes at him you are neither entertained nor humored by the sub-standard comedy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: moving on , there is val ( christina ricci ) and stephie , ( gabby hoffman ) 2 teenage girls with fake identification and very different thoughts .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: val is monica's cousin and a true fan of the new york scene .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: on the other hand , stephie is convinced that she is vulnerable to crime when the two venture out of their usual locations in search of the party that they just can't find .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: paradoxically , it is 2 punks that they meet at a bar ( actually they attempt to flee from their presence , but aren't successful ) who guide them through their fears and force a level of relaxation upon their warped minds .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: of all the insanely dull and uninteresting couples , only one approaches a level of decency in both acting and plot .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: wisely , the movie's creators have put heavy emphasis on lucy ( courtney love ) and kevin ( paul rudd ) who are best friends and share the common bond of being dateless .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: paul has just broken up with long time steady ellie ( janeane garofalo ) and is starting to come to terms with his loss when lucy informs him that ellie had been sleeping around during their relationship .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , the only complexity to these two characters is that they seem to want to be more than friends , and that is reiterated when they attempt sexual intercourse in a bathroom stall on more than one occasion during this strange evening .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: finally , there are the two worst performances and worst sub-plot of the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: jack ( jay mohr ) and cindy ( kate hudson ) have been going out for a short period of time and jack just learned that he took cindy's virginity the night before .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: while she attempts to play this down and be her usual self , he is a predictably self loathing male as he attempts to deal with a string of one night stands that includes the recently deflowered cindy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: very often , when a film is as putrid as this production , there will at least be a decent quality of film making to reveal an occasional moment of glory .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , this film has neither the quality of cinematography nor the moments of glory to be highlighted .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: instead , what you get is a collection of rough and inconsistent cuts , bad continuity and inaccuracies .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: first , and most noticeable is that as the film goes from one subplot to another , there is no apparent order that it follows , and it is also weekened by unnecessarily edgy edits from scene to scene and shot to shot .

docs.text: at other times , objects seem to get up and move and hairstyles and costumes change from shot to shot .

docs.text: there are also at least 4 scenes in a taxi cab that go from start to finish .

docs.text: not in a single one of them does anybody pay the driver .

docs.text: and yet , no matter how miserable this film may be , and no matter how poor the acting is all around , there was a ray of a hope for these many bad plots .

docs.text: perhaps , if the makers had just decided to concentrate on one or two or , perhaps , even three , there might have been the time and opportunity for some character development , or quality acting , or even a decent plot payoff at the end .
